(* Beginning of Notebook Content *)
Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Model V1 - Self-Balancing Tail with Variable Length", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.929354612578005*^9, 3.929354616192994*^9}, {
  3.929355210549653*^9, 3.9293552190879917`*^9}, {3.9918429510719347`*^9, 
  3.991842958992612*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"067356c3-28ca-4144-be02-\
7957e03610f3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["(*diagrams TBD*)\n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "\nBefore changing the angle of the tail or adding more joints, we need to \
understand how balance works. In physics, balance is achieved by having a net \
torque of zero in our system. In this case, our system is defined as the \
following: with a center of mass for the tail offset by a distance and a \
center of mass for the head offset by a distance and height. For all \
calculations, we will use SI units.\n\nFrom this setup, we must derive an \
equation that can be used. In this setup, the six main variables are:\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d3a218c4-41f3-43af-8251-ca126d82a3b6"],
 " - the mass of the head.\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["d", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "043508de-5fd4-4e73-a986-381fe8f39b7a"],
 " - the horizontal distance from the point mass of the head to the body.\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2d5bdb53-56df-4057-9d10-36d835a93931"],
 " - the vertical distance from the point mass of the head to the body.\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e04d9068-6d37-40ba-b60d-05dae9824814"],
 " - the mass of the tail.\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bdf3ce6d-0887-4132-9f5f-f159b10b1aeb"],
 " - the horizontal distance from the point mass of the tail to the body. It\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s important to note that the center of mass for the tail is \
this value divided by two as it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s not a point mass.\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e23a3094-eee7-4171-8c24-bf53ce777e70"],
 " - the vertical distance from the point mass of the tail to the body.\n\n\
However, our monkey will not always be standing. Thus, we need to factor in a \
7th variable, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9014cda8-3bed-4c8e-8ae7-cc15cd3e73ca"],
 ". In our diagram, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "88e7eff0-baa4-4419-83f5-9eb70d30513e"],
 " looks like this:\n\nWith the variables setup, we can begin calculations. \
Because there are only two masses in the system, the head and the tail, the \
torque equation looks like this: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cd99f442-28cb-4c6f-bc85-4796c408e252"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "817a813e-0a10-4092-83da-c383120e1fc3"],
 "\n\nSubstituting in the equation that torque is \[Tau] = F*r*sin(\[Theta]), \
we can calculate our radii (r) as this:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "60ae99d5-91bf-4f1f-b23e-c13bfd7fcd07"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SqrtBox[
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      SubscriptBox["d", "head"], "2"], " ", "+", " ", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      SubscriptBox["h", "head"], "2"]}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e6c70c5c-cbda-49a5-821f-4a5161a3717e"],
 "\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "12cddac9-a804-4811-94b0-0aac5322853c"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SqrtBox[
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       FractionBox[
        SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], "2"], ")"}], "2"], " ", "+", " ", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      SubscriptBox["h", "tail"], "2"]}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ddf1b52a-f8c3-4576-b6ab-26325d881ece"],
 "\n\nCalculating for \[Theta] is slightly harder. The angle for the \
components of gravity is not the exact angle that the radius makes with the \
long leg & short leg of the triangle. We can use alternate interior angles to \
model the system as the following, with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3bfd5ab1-43ff-4996-bf70-862875fbd56d"],
 " as the temporary one representing the \[Theta] in the head equation and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "t"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "217b9b72-a604-4a0b-86b7-93034fc212d5"],
 " representing the tail equation. Using trigonometric identities, both of \
these will eventually be replaced.\n\n\nWith ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "t"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e2599c8f-2b23-4e35-a390-5b89975eb1a6"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4e7e04f8-dbee-49c0-b09d-a0c2273e4285"],
 " defined, we can plug them into the torque equations and simplify from \
there. Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s begin with the head equation.\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a4d1b42b-5f5a-4420-929b-29d115249527"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a2e7d326-8113-4b1e-9a75-169aa46c8218"],
 " * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "14bac94c-5994-4694-8ff8-f25113d52dfe"],
 " * sin(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "h"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "23ef66f7-cd9a-4586-bc22-41dddf3de4f1"],
 ")\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f69dc05c-d103-45e5-bbf9-f097ec217f0b"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "80e30a3a-92f0-4ab9-911f-79fcbe564736"],
 " * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ee57d3f1-5e8b-44b9-9861-46ef566d1aa0"],
 " * sin(arctan(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["d", "head"], 
    SubscriptBox["h", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "70757adb-b720-42d6-9200-7bd2fd5bd3a0"],
 ")+",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "336ba21a-88e3-4391-9155-b2c47327cdc1"],
 ")\n\nInside of the sine function is an addition of two angles. Using this, \
we can expand, and then simplify it with the sum of sines identity:\nsin(A+B) \
= sinAcosB + cosAsinB\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "26c5868a-931e-484b-ba58-60720c9827b9"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9e7c7e13-ebbe-4823-b89a-e1cf29be7702"],
 " * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "27e8e07b-3326-4a87-851f-5be2716894b2"],
 " * (sin(arctan(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["d", "head"], 
    SubscriptBox["h", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9e409477-d7a9-4d59-8cf5-e8220570849f"],
 ")cos(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7af5a761-e1c2-4fdc-9b86-04cf5ed4acd1"],
 ")+cos(arctan(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["d", "head"], 
    SubscriptBox["h", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3eb732c4-d5e0-4cd4-8f1c-24a6690a0b81"],
 ")sin(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d6bc23d8-56cf-409a-a679-1e8169105a45"],
 "))\n\nIt seems complex, but the sine and cosine of arctan(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["d", "head"], 
    SubscriptBox["h", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "74523365-32ac-4a99-9573-9d62774b773f"],
 ") can actually be defined using ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8964a6d0-dde9-4010-95de-a0fdf115ee2c"],
 "! Let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s examine that with the diagram below:\n\nWe end up \
with:\n\nsin(arctan(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["d", "head"], 
    SubscriptBox["h", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a849575d-6866-4d52-be95-63cfb98b5f1c"],
 ")) = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["d", "head"], 
    SubscriptBox["r", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f480c53e-8a9d-4196-9b32-adeab867e438"],
 "\n\ncos(arctan(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["d", "head"], 
    SubscriptBox["h", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b766ae8d-bbe8-45a8-b7d8-e90501c67d3a"],
 ")) = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["h", "head"], 
    SubscriptBox["r", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "808aa509-cc17-4411-9760-00ef5a0b2898"],
 "\n\nGiven this, let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s plug it in to the equation.\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ec4ab493-b79c-4a0f-825d-1368a87a94b3"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7f4d5adb-39cd-4773-9c42-dc2cbeff311d"],
 " * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "561f45c4-02d4-415c-81b8-556a6272bb3d"],
 " * (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["d", 
      RowBox[{"head", " "}]], "*", " ", 
     RowBox[{"cos", "(", 
      FormBox[
       SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
       TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], 
    SubscriptBox["r", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "259d143d-7ceb-43de-ada0-1311ed2b5d7f"],
 "+",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["h", 
      RowBox[{"head", " "}]], "*", " ", 
     RowBox[{"sin", "(", 
      FormBox[
       SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
       TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], 
    SubscriptBox["r", "head"]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ac3dc3d5-9e44-408d-bdc2-5cabddc9cc2c"],
 ")\n\nSince every part of the identity has r_head on the denominator, and we \
are multiplying it by r_head, we get a much simpler equation for the torque \
of the head:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "45168eb4-cf8e-4083-ac33-b82f28f3c9c2"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5f4a4e91-d4b1-4094-913e-725014bda9d1"],
 " * (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["d", 
     RowBox[{"head", " "}]], "*", " ", 
    RowBox[{"cos", "(", 
     FormBox[
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
      TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d22bcbeb-de61-43c0-901a-2d52210ba1e2"],
 "+",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["h", 
     RowBox[{"head", " "}]], "*", " ", 
    RowBox[{"sin", "(", 
     FormBox[
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
      TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "89d362e4-0876-48bf-831d-62a0ea4fabfb"],
 ")\n\nThe torque of the tail is the same, except instead of adding the two \
angles, we must subtract them, as the diagram shows. This means we use the \
difference of sines identity, sin(A-B) = sinAcosB-cosAsinB. We also must \
remember that the distance (d_head) is divided by two:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2fe33266-ce25-43ca-929a-bf815807ff42"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "73d4e8d7-4dbe-427f-932d-a25f3e41ffd6"],
 " * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "51d6f5e9-ef16-462b-bce3-8b9e7cf85c45"],
 " * sin(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "t"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5908c0d2-26f1-442a-b080-e11f6affcc30"],
 ")\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "775393f4-f583-4580-bce4-72b02f1e4a35"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fe0bfc02-a640-4e65-bf4b-ae8b42f78ef1"],
 " * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b2e1aaf3-b6ab-49cc-a185-959d8b2c4cff"],
 " * sin(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"arctan", "(", 
     FormBox[
      FractionBox[
       SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], 
       RowBox[{"2", 
        SubscriptBox["h", "tail"]}]],
      TraditionalForm], ")"}], "-", 
    FormBox[
     SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
     TraditionalForm]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "86bf9615-88e4-4318-8650-2a86d8b9b8b2"],
 ")\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3475061d-6853-42ee-b769-7007b82d3447"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b24f2fc5-65ca-4025-830f-856d1cd16293"],
 " * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "06cc80dd-0c0b-47af-b413-81e2445fbff2"],
 " * (sin(arctan(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], 
    RowBox[{"2", 
     SubscriptBox["h", "tail"]}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5f88962c-650a-4d88-8484-2222b5e524fe"],
 ")cos(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "96032a2c-b6f0-458d-be1c-8fe24146eed0"],
 ")-cos(arctan(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], 
    RowBox[{"2", 
     SubscriptBox["h", "tail"]}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fef1e4f9-9f02-40e7-acd1-a59b1d83d23e"],
 ")sin(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1c5da6d1-a32d-4bf0-b7f4-0cbf91a797b8"],
 "))\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0f28fc8e-d604-4542-bd37-ca1a92b68b52"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c7757307-30fe-4a8a-83bf-5ba7c93353e4"],
 " * ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["r", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ac29b497-c31f-4324-90ae-ed252e43309c"],
 " * (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], 
     RowBox[{"cos", "(", 
      FormBox[
       SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
       TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"2", 
     SubscriptBox["r", "tail"]}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f080da26-3195-419e-8ed4-2dbf567983af"],
 "-",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["h", "tail"], 
     RowBox[{"sin", "(", 
      FormBox[
       SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
       TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"2", 
     SubscriptBox["r", "tail"]}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "01728db2-375a-4e20-928f-5bbe71e2be22"],
 ")\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4120ad6f-2be4-42e6-82d8-a12a5b74e908"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fe3bf41f-c14e-463b-b344-8802d7d0d98d"],
 " *  (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], 
    RowBox[{"cos", "(", 
     FormBox[
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
      TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "89446bf6-d5f4-45f5-abde-6ee247d2dab4"],
 "-",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["h", "tail"], 
    RowBox[{"sin", "(", 
     FormBox[
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
      TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "eee8df93-95bd-4658-9483-668174ae49c0"],
 ")\n\nThe finished model is the following, where we set both torques equal \
to each other.\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ddeb9c4e-0670-4a65-9945-54f8b5cac18d"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "head"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b7f7560b-bbce-4b7d-9ca4-8fd0d71fd124"],
 " * (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["d", 
     RowBox[{"head", " "}]], "*", " ", 
    RowBox[{"cos", "(", 
     FormBox[
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
      TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1579d73c-4c9a-4363-9495-7e3debc5e606"],
 "+",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["h", 
     RowBox[{"head", " "}]], "*", " ", 
    RowBox[{"sin", "(", 
     FormBox[
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
      TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b2c86ced-b856-4328-9544-dfda1a57b034"],
 ") = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "56034b5e-86c1-4020-8e73-e9ec9e1e977e"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["m", "tail"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "71a68633-cf36-44b2-ab07-4a5621dd0961"],
 " *  (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["d", "tail"], 
    RowBox[{"cos", "(", 
     FormBox[
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
      TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "588ce977-3d41-4142-8f0b-81432cb80eea"],
 "-",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["h", "tail"], 
    RowBox[{"sin", "(", 
     FormBox[
      SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "lean"],
      TraditionalForm], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e3b2a391-9194-41d5-9149-f7b293615277"],
 ")\n\nTo model the monkey tilting itself, we must change \[Theta]_tail. If \
we changed \[Theta]_tail, the system would just fall. To accommodate for \
this, we must make one or more of the six variables unknown such that the \
model can automatically adjust it to keep the torques in equilibrium. In this \
example, we will solve for d_tail as our unknown variable.\n\nThis will be \
achieved with the Wolfram Language. To start the simulation, we define the \
constants = all variables besides d_tail."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9293546184036617`*^9, 3.9293546199188967`*^9}, {
   3.991843023893482*^9, 3.991843098671399*^9}, {3.991843141651308*^9, 
   3.991843153204752*^9}, {3.9918432145448112`*^9, 3.991843314639442*^9}, {
   3.991843367531785*^9, 3.991843482849601*^9}, {3.991843529523225*^9, 
